# Beckn Protocol — Suggested Reading Order
#
# This is the single source of truth for the order in which RFC documents
# are presented in docs/README.md "Suggested Order of Reading".
#
# Format:
#   - One entry per line, in the form `Filename.md|Display Title`.
#   - The `|` separator is required. Title is the curated display title used
#     in docs/README.md — it does NOT have to match the document's H1.
#   - Lines starting with `#` and blank lines are ignored.
#   - Order in this file = order in the rendered README section.
#
# Workflow:
#   1. Edit this file to add, remove, or reorder entries.
#   2. Run `python3 scripts/update_readme.py` to regenerate docs/README.md.
#      Existing curated descriptions are preserved by filename match.
#   3. New entries get a TODO description placeholder that you must fill in
#      before committing — the pre-commit hook will reject TODO placeholders.
#
# The pre-commit hook also runs `update_readme.py` and re-stages docs/README.md
# whenever this file or any docs/*.md file is staged.

Introduction.md|Specification: Architecture, Design Philosophy and Principles
Keyword_Definitions.md|Keyword Definitions
The_Beckn_Protocol_Stack.md|The Beckn Protocol Stack
Core_Data_Schema.md|Core Data Schema
Linked_Data_Schema.md|Linked Data Schema
API.md|Beckn API Endpoints
Authentication_and_Trust.md|Authentication and Trust
Error_Codes.md|Handling Exceptions and Errors
Design_Guide.md|Specification Design Guide
Schema_Design_Guide.md|Schema Design Guide
RFC_Authoring_Guide.md|RFC Authoring Guide
RFC_Template.md|RFC Template
